article.headline: Canady leads early run as Old Dominion routs Norfolk State
article.linkText: Old Dominion stretches home winning streak to 28
article.story:
NORFOLK, Va. -- Jessica Canady scored eight of her 24 points during a 22-3 run to start the game and Old Dominion (No. 20 ESPN/USA Today, No. 23 AP) routed Norfolk State 97-54 on Sunday to stretch its home winning streak to 28 games.

The Lady Monarchs (4-2) led 44-20 at halftime and by 47 as they dominated in every facet of the game. Canady added 19 rebounds, and Tiffany Green had 21 points and eight rebounds.

Whitney Long led the Spartans (0-4) with 19 points, but she had four of her team's 30 turnovers. Norfolk State was outrebounded 67-37.

Jazzmin Walters added 14 points and Jasmine Parker 12 for Old Dominion, which was coming off a 74-48 loss at No. 24 Michigan State.
